CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper October 22, 1955, pg. 7, reads: "Centre - Roberts Staff - The Centre-Roberts Garage, 72 Roberts Street, manned by factory-trained mechanics, is one of the finest and most modern garages in Pittsburgh.  The new establishment will hold its grand opening Saturday, Oct. 22.  Left to right, part of the factory-trained staff: Willie Cummings, F. Paye, Camuel (Spuddy) Spearman and Joe Talley - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: F. Paye, Joe Talley, Camuel or Samuel "Spuddy" Spearman, and Willie Cummings working on car in Centre - Roberts Garage, 72 Roberts Street, Hill District
